    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{9, 14, 5, 4, -20, -13, -5, 13\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{9 + 14 + 5 + 4 + (-20) + (-13) + (-5) + 13}{8}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{9 + 14 + 5 + 4 - 20 - 13 - 5 + 13}{8} = \\frac{14}{8} = 1.75\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n(9 - 1.75)^2 = 7.25^2 = 52.5625 \\\\\n(14 - 1.75)^2 = 12.25^2 = 150.0625 \\\\\n(5 - 1.75)^2 = 3.25^2 = 10.5625 \\\\\n(4 - 1.75)^2 = 2.25^2 = 5.0625 \\\\\n(-20 - 1.75)^2 = (-21.75)^2 = 473.0625 \\\\\n(-13 - 1.75)^2 = (-14.75)^2 = 217.5625 \\\\\n(-5 - 1.75)^2 = (-6.75)^2 = 45.5625 \\\\\n(13 - 1.75)^2 = 11.25^2 = 126.5625\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n52.5625 + 150.0625 + 10.5625 + 5.0625 + 473.0625 + 217.5625 + 45.5625 + 126.5625 = 908.5\n$$"
